com.android.layoutlib.bridge

Class Bridge

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.android.ide.common.rendering.api.Bridge
      • com.android.layoutlib.bridge.Bridge

  • public final class Bridge
extends com.android.ide.common.rendering.api.Bridge
    Main entry point of the LayoutLib Bridge.

    To use this bridge, simply instantiate an object of type Bridge and call #createScene(SceneParams)

        public RenderSession createSession(SessionParams params)
        Starts a layout session by inflating and rendering it. The method returns a RenderSession on which further actions can be taken.
        Parameters:
        params - the SessionParams object with all the information necessary to create the scene.
        Returns:
        a new RenderSession object that contains the result of the layout.

      • prepareThread

        public static void prepareThread()
        Prepares the current thread for rendering. Note that while this can be called several time, the first call to cleanupThread() will do the clean-up, and make the thread unable to do further scene actions.

      • cleanupThread

        public static void cleanupThread()
        Cleans up thread-specific data. After this, the thread cannot be used for scene actions.

        Note that it doesn't matter how many times prepareThread() was called, a single call to this will prevent the thread from doing further scene actions
